SCU PE Club

What is the SCU PE Club?

The Santa Clara University Physical Education Club is a club that is not affiliated with SCU and it is devoted to getting students an outlet from their busy lives around campus. The SCU PE Club provides structure, social interaction, and physical activity for students who are slammed with school work, homesick, or just need a friend.











Last meeting: Trampoline Park!

Last week we went to Rockin' Jump Trampoline Park in San Jose. We played dodgeball, basketball, tag, and toilet tag on the trampolines. Participants helped out the local community by entertaining the kids and watching them for their parents in the trampoline park. It was a lot of fun.













SCUrito Prize!

Every week, there is a SCU burrito from Benson Dining Hall awarded to the winner of the challenge played that week. When there is no clear winner, the SCUrito prize will be awarded to the participant with the best sportsmanship! Last weeks winner was Megan Nuchereno!
